    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix potential deadlock in cp_gtp_tunnel function\n\n### Summary\nThere is a deadlock caused by inconsistent lock acquisition ordering downstream of function cp_gtp_tunnel. When calling cp_gtp_tunnel() the behavior is not what is expected. The issue may be in cp_gtp_tunnel or a function downstream/upstream of it.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/rrc_gNB_NGAP.c`: Fixed buffer overflow in cp_gtp_tunnel by adding bounds checking and changed parameter passing to use pointer instead of value\n- `openair2/RRC/NR/rrc_gNB_NGAP.c`: Applied same buffer overflow fix to handover request acknowledge transfer code\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder high load conditions with multiple UE contexts being processed simultaneously, the system may experience deadlocks when processing GTP tunnel information. Symptoms include:\n- RRC processing threads becoming unresponsive\n- NGAP messages not being processed\n- Memory corruption in tunnel address handling\n- System becoming unstable requiring restart\n\nThe issue is most likely to occur when:\n1. Multiple PDU sessions are being established concurrently\n2. Tunnel address information contains invalid length values\n3. Buffer overflows corrupt adjacent memory structures\n4. Inconsistent lock ordering occurs during ITTI message processing\n\n"
}